cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the diffusion of information across different online social media services and the network formed by users who participate in cross-pollination. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper studies user behavior and involvement in sharing information across different social networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the diffusion of different types of multimedia content (videos, photos) across social networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with the popularity and diffusion of information across different platforms. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also a possible category as the paper analyzes the diffusion of multimedia content across different online platforms and networks.
